{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a moderate sum of money, with partial restitution already made. While the crime involves a breach of trust, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to the amount embezzled and the defendant's clean record. Sentencing guidelines for this type of white-collar crime typically favor a shorter custodial term combined with supervised release and a mandate for full restitution. A 6-month period of incarceration is sufficient to provide a punitive deterrent while allowing for the defendant to return to the workforce to pay back the remaining balance.",
  "verdict": 6
}
